tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE user_profiles ( 
    user_id INT PRIMARY KEY, 
    first_name TEXT, 
    last_name TEXT, 
    email TEXT UNIQUE, 
    age INT, 
    gender TEXT, 
    height FLOAT, 
    weight FLOAT, 
    preferences TEXT[] 
);

CREATE TABLE user_profiles (
    user_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    first_name VARCHAR(50),
    last_name VARCHAR(50),
    email VARCHAR(100),
    phone_number VARCHAR(15)
);

CREATE TABLE user_preferences (
    preference_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id INT,
    color_preference VARCHAR(20),
    material_preference VARCHAR(20),
    size_preference VARCHAR(10),
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES user_profiles(user_id)
);

CREATE TABLE user_preferences ( 
    preference_id INT PRIMARY KEY, 
    user_id INT, 
    preference_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL, 
    preference_value TEXT, 
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES user_profiles(user_id) 
);

CREATE TABLE printing_orders ( 
    order_id INT PRIMARY KEY, 
    user_id INT, 
    file_name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL, 
    order_date TIMESTAMP, 
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES user_profiles(user_id) 
);

CREATE TABLE user_profiles (
    user_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    first_name VARCHAR(50),
    last_name VARCHAR(50),
    email VARCHAR(100)
)

CREATE TABLE user_preferences (
    user_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    color_preference VARCHAR(50),
    material_preference VARCHAR(50),
    size_preference VARCHAR(50)
)

CREATE TABLE orders (
    order_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id INT REFERENCES user_profiles(user_id),
    item_name VARCHAR(100),
    quantity INT,
    price DECIMAL(10, 2)
)

CREATE TABLE prints (
    print_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    order_id INT REFERENCES orders(order_id),
    file_path VARCHAR(255),
    print_status VARCHAR(20)
)

CREATE TABLE UserPreferences (
    preference_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id INT REFERENCES Users(user_id),
    print_resolution VARCHAR(20) NOT NULL,
    fill_density FLOAT NOT NULL,
    color_preference VARCHAR(20)
);

CREATE TABLE PrintJobs (
    job_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id INT REFERENCES Users(user_id),
    printer_id INT REFERENCES Printers(printer_id),
    job_status VARCHAR(20) NOT NULL,
    start_time TIMESTAMP,
    end_time TIMESTAMP
);
